  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>RMSSD Normal Breathing</measure>
    <time_frame>t-4,5 hours</time_frame>
    <description>Root Mean Square of the Successive Differences (RMSSD) is one of a few time-domain tools used to assess heart rate variability, the successive differences being neighboring RR or pulse intervals.
It is calculated as the square root of the mean of the squares of the successive differences between adjacent RR intervals or pulse intervals.
In this study pulse intervals were measured non-invasively during five minutes, while subjects were supine, breathing regularly.
Measurements were done at two timepoints t=0 and t=4,5hours. RMSSD was compared between these two timepoints.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
